    {
      "type": "bulleted-list",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "What were the social, economic, and political forces that contributed to urban decay in the 1970s?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "What were some of the hardships faced by urban residents in the late 1970s and early 1980s?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "How and why did the urban crisis particularly affect African Americans and Latinos?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "What were some of the political reforms that were proposed or attempted to address the problems of the cities? What might have been the sources of resistance to these efforts?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
